31/03/2003
OTTAWA, Canada -- Prime Minister Jean Chretien said on Saturday (29 March) the country had ratified NATO accession protocols with seven Central and Eastern European countries, including Romania and Bulgaria.
Canada became the first member country to endorse the agreements, which opened the way to the largest ever NATO expansion.
The candidate countries and the ambassadors of 19 NATO members signed the protocols on 26 March.
The new partners are to join the alliance in 2004.
(BTA, Rompres, AFP - 29/03/03)
